pageContext.claim: “And as soon as I endorsed him, they wanted to move the election. They didn't want to move the election. As soon as I endorsed him, the Wisconsin Democrats say, 'Oh, let's move the election to two months later.' They didn't mind having the election until I endorsed him, which is very interesting.”
pageContext.analysis: There’s no evidence that the governor wanted to move the election for any other reason than fear of spreading coronavirus. Plus, Trump first endorsed Kelly — who lost by a wide margin — in January.
